Just a quick scroll through the Twitter account of City Power shows a substantial increase in outages recently. To find out what lies at the heart of this, we took to the streets to find out more. eNCA’s Lee McCabe compiled this report. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The power's been going out all over Johannesburg this past week. Affected communities include Newlands, Coronationville and Devland in Soweto, READ: SA's Electricity Crisis | Power cuts to continue City Power says it's becoming increasingly difficult to police and secure mini-substations. Cable theft and illegal connections cost the city R3.6-billion a year. * eNCA's Lee McCabe reports.